    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. so if i have a lot of stuff just sitting there not moving, what are some specific ways i can fix that? like how do i stop stock from just piling up?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can't stop the pile-up entirely, but you can stop the *growing* pile-up by making your stockroom a place where the \"little goblins\" of the inventory are forced to move, not just sit and rot.\n\nFirst, you need to understand that in the world of fashion, inventory is not a resource; it is a **time bomb**. If you have a lot of stuff sitting there, you aren't just holding onto clothes; you are holding onto *potential* sales that are slowly turning into dead weight. The goblins in your closet are not just waiting for a customer; they are waiting for a *reason* to move, and if there is no reason, they will eventually decide to leave.\n\nTo fix this, you need to implement a system that forces the goblins to move. Here are some specific ways to stop the stock from piling up:\n\n1.  **Implement a \"Sell-First, Buy-Last\" Rule**: This is the most important rule for a boutique. You cannot buy new stock until you have sold the old stock. If you have a pile of 500 items, you must sell 500 before you buy 500. This",
      "source": "target",
